<div class="section">
	<div class="container">
		<h2>Sign up</h2>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="span4">
				<%= simple_form_for(resource, :as => resource_name, :url => registration_path(resource_name), :html => {:class => 'form-vertical' }) do |f| %>
				  <%= f.error_notification %>
				  <%= display_base_errors resource %>
				  <%= f.association :roles, :collection => ["Viewer", "Manager"],
				    :value_method => lambda { |el| Role.find_by_name(el).id }, :as => :radio_buttons, :required => true, :checked => Role.find_by_name("Viewer").id  %>
				  <%= f.input :name, :autofocus => true, :required => true %>
				  <%= f.input :email, :required => true %>
				  <%= f.input :password, :required => true %>
				  <%= f.input :password_confirmation, :required => true %>
				  <%= f.button :submit, 'Sign up', :class => 'btn-primary' %>
				<% end %>
				<%= render "devise/shared/links" %>
			</div>
			<div class="span8"> 
				<h3>Accounts</h3>
				<div class="row">
					<div class="span8">
						<h4>Viewer</h4>
						<p>A viewer account can only view plans that managers have uploaded to Plan Source.  This user doesn't have print priveleges and cannot edit, update, create or destroy plans.  Typically this user is invited to Plan Source by a manager and is then shared plans and jobs with.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="row">
					<div class="span8">
						<h4>Manager</h4>
						<p>A manager account has all of the priveleges of a viewer but can also manage plans and jobs, and can share jobs with other manager or viewer accounts.  This user has print priveleges and can edit, update, create, or destroy plans.  Typically this user is a project manager and intends to invite other users to be viewers of his jobs.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>